            "title": "Cultural expertise, law and rights : a comprehensive guide",
            "abstract": [
                "Preface / Kamari Clarke -- Introduction / Livia Holden -- What is Cultural Expertise? / Livia Holden -- Cultural Expertise and Ethics / Charmaine Cole -- Cultural Expertise as Decolonisation / Rama Srinivasan -- Cultural Expertise and Race / ChorSwang Ngin -- Cultural Expertise and LGBTQ+ / Victoria McCloud -- Cultural Expertise and Female Genital Cuttin/Female Genital Mutilation / Ruth Mestre, Lotta Wendel and Sara Johnsdotter -- Cultural Expertise and Multiculturalism / Ralph Grillo -- Cultural Expertise and Language / Patrick Heinrich -- Cultural Expertise and the Media / Ma\u0142gorzata Lisowska-Magdziarz -- Cultural Expertise and Investigative Journalism / Ticky Monekosso -- Cultural Expertise and Procedural Justice / Stanis\u0142aw Burdziej -- Cultural Expertise in Asylum and Refugee Laws / John R Campbell -- Cultural Expertise and Terrorism Investigations / Ariel Planeix -- Cultural Expertise and Extreme Speech / Max Steuer -- Cultural Expertise and Commercial Arbitration / Giorgio Fabio Colombo -- Cultural Expertise and International Criminal Law / Joshua Isaac Bishay -- Cultural Expertise and International Human Rights Law / Noora Araj\u00e4rvi -- Cultural Expertise and Indigenous Rights / Noelle Higgins -- Cultural Expertise and Conflict Resolution / Susan F. Hirsch and Brigit R. A. Moore -- Cultural Expertise in Europe / Livia Holden -- Cultural Expertise and Indigenous People in Australia / David S. Trigger -- Cultural Expertise and History in Australia / Tanya Josev -- Cultural Expertise in South Africa / Christa Rautenbach -- Cultural Expertise and Indigenous Ecologies / Aur\u00e9lien Bouayad -- Cultural Expertise in the United States / ChorSwang Ngin -- Cultural Expertise in Chile Roberto / \u00c1lvarez San Mart\u00edn -- Cultural Expertise in South Asia / Mary Kavita Dominic -- Cultural Expertise in the Arab Middle East / Dina Haddad -- Cultural Expertise in Islamic Courts in Indonesia / Euis Nurlaelawati and Witriani Afterword -- Afterword : Cultural Expertise Within, and Beyond, the Boundaries of Law / Mark Goodale Inde.",
                "Cultural Expertise, Law, and Rights introduces readers to the theory and practice of cultural expertise in the resolution of conflicts and the claim of rights in diverse societies. Combining theory and case-studies of the use of cultural expertise in real situations, and in a great variety of fields, this is the first book to offer a comprehensive examination of the field of cultural expertise: its intellectual orientations, practical applications and ethical implications. This book engages an extensive and interdisciplinary variety of topics \u2013 ranging from race, language, sexuality, Indigenous rights and women\u2019s rights to immigration and asylum laws, international commercial arbitration and criminal law. It also offers a truly global perspective covering cultural expertise in Africa, Asia, Australia, Europe, Latin America, the Middle East and North America. Finally, the book offers theoretical and practical guidance for the ethical use of cultural expert knowledge. This is an essential volume for teachers and students in the social sciences \u2013 especially law, anthropology, and sociology \u2013 and members of the legal professions who engage in cross-cultural dispute resolution, asylum and migration, private international law and other fields of law in which cultural arguments play a role."
            ],
